### Issue

- **What did you do?**
I'm trying to tune hyperparamater and see if I can implement grid search myself. In order to do that, I would like to fit the model in multiple threads by using Parallel.For

- **What happened?**
However, I realized that fitting the model multiple times using Parallel.For takes much longer than a single threaded for loop. In a for loop. my CPU utilization is at around 30% all the time, while using Parallel.For, it spikes to 100% at first, then drops down to 6% for quite some time, then jumps back to 30% and finishes. Am I not supposed to fit in parallel? If that is the case then what is the best way to do grid search?

### Source code / logs

Single threaded for - takes 20 seconds

```
for (var i = 0; i < 100; i++) {
    var pipeline = CreatePipeline();
    pipeline.Fit(dataView);
}
```

Parallel.For - takes 56 seconds

```
Parallel.For(0, 100, i => {
    var pipeline = CreatePipeline();
    pipeline.Fit(dataView);
});
```

